China Appoints Presidents of Cnooc, Sinopec Parent Companies

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-24T03:12:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/cnooc-chief-yang-hua-picked-by-government-as-president-of-parent-company.html
China appointed China Petroleum &
Chemical Corp.’s vice president, Wang Tianpu, as president of
the parent company also known as Sinopec Group,  according  to the
group’s online newsletter today.  Separately, the government appointed  Cnooc Ltd. (883) ’s Chief
Executive Officer Yang Hua as president of China National
Offshore Oil Corp., Cnooc’s parent company, the Hong Kong-listed
company said on its  website  yesterday.  China had reshuffled the top management of the two state-
owned  oil companies  in April. Su Shulin resigned as president of
China Petrochemical Corp., or Sinopec Group, and chairman of
China Petroleum, also known as Sinopec, to become acting
governor of  Fujian province . Fu Chengyu resigned as president of
China National Offshore to become the chairman of Sinopec Group
and Sinopec.  Wang Yilin, a former vice president at China National
Petroleum Corp., became the chairman of China National Offshore
and Cnooc after Fu’s departure in April.  The government made the announcements on Aug. 22, according
to the two companies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chua Baizhen in Beijing at 
